<SysML:Block id="0c8672c7-f965-11f0-8c18-1063c8f53908">
<name>
<val>ESC</val>
</name>
<nestingClass>
<ref refid="5c5f2d19-f964-11f0-b450-1063c8f53908"/>
</nestingClass>
<note>
<val>Electronic Speed Controller

C.ntrols motor rotation speeds - receives power from nattery and control from FC. Usually paired with the FC in a single chip.

Main value is its AMP value, showing how much energy can be pushed through it. To calculate it, you take motor watt numbers and devide by the battery voltage you are running.</val>
</note>
